### Area

admin/api

### Describe the bug

When you trigger `POST https://{HOST_NAME}/auth/admin/realms/conundrum/clients/{CLIENT}/authz/resource-server/policy/evaluate` with invalid `{USER_ID}` (not exists) 

```
{
  "resources": [
    {
      "_id": "{RESOURCE_ID}",
      "scopes": [
        "{SCOPE}"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "context": {
    "attributes": {}
  },
  "roleIds": [],
  "clientId": "{CLIENT_ID}",
  "userId": "{USER_ID}",
  "entitlements": false
}
```

Reason of this bug is expection about `getUserFromToken()` in `KeycloakIdentity`. 

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/669347/211058769-f2f2c25f-f4fe-4ca9-8da5-78ea03387126.png)


### Version

1.18

### Expected behavior

Error that describe "User not found"

### Actual behavior

NPE, 500 error

### How to Reproduce?

```

POST https://{HOST_NAME}/auth/admin/realms/conundrum/clients/{CLIENT}/authz/resource-server/policy/evaluate


{
  "resources": [
    {
      "_id": "{RESOURCE_ID}",
      "scopes": [
        "{SCOPE}"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "context": {
    "attributes": {}
  },
  "roleIds": [],
  "clientId": "{CLIENT_ID}",
  "userId": "{PUT_RANDOM_UUID_HERE}",
  "entitlements": false
}
```

